text.section:
The board shall:
Adopt and provide itself with a seal with a band inscribed, "Kentucky Board of Landscape Architects" with the coat of arms of the state in the center;
Keep a complete record of its proceedings and an accurate list of all applications made, licenses issued, inactive and retired licenses, and licenses disciplined;
Make a general report including finances to the Governor annually; and
Employ legal counsel or contract for legal services it considers necessary.
